properties.Name: ExperianCompanyUccFiling
properties.Description:
Uniform Commercial Code (UCC) filings allow creditors to notify other creditors about a debtor's assets used as collateral for a secured transaction.

 UCC liens filed with secretary of state offices act as a public notice by the "creditor" of the creditor's interest in the property.

Columns.Name: ExperianFileNumber
Columns.Description: The unique and persistent number that identifies and tracks the Experian company.

Columns.Name: ProfileTimestamp
Columns.Description: The timestamp of the Experian profile.

Columns.Name: UccContinuedDate
Columns.Description: The date of the UCC continuance.

Columns.Name: JurisdictionName
Columns.Description:
The name of the filing jurisdiction.

Ex:
- SEC OF STATE DELAWARE

Columns.Name: SecuredPartyName
Columns.Description:
The name of the secured.

Ex:
Secured Party: NATIONAL CREDIT CORPORATION NJ PARSIPPANY 07054

Columns.Name: CollateralDescription
Columns.Description:
A description of the collateral related to the filing.

Ex:
Collateral: EQUIP, HEREAFTER ACQUIRED PROP

Properties.Description:
Uniform Commercial Code (UCC) filings allow creditors to notify other creditors about a debtor's assets used as collateral for a secured transaction.

 UCC liens filed with secretary of state offices act as a public notice by the "creditor" of the creditor's interest in the property.
